This reimagined Carousel by @imcalledtoffee and @repertoryphilippines stripped the classic Broadway musical off to its barest, exposed it for what it truly is, and hit hard where it matters the most. 

There are so many reasons why you should watch this show (the staging, direction and choreography are superb) but I dont want to spoil it for those who are about to see it.  @anakarylle and @gianmagdangal deliver the performance of their lives here while @mikkievolante and @_lorenzmartinez deliver punches left and right.  Every single person in this cast of 14 shines so brightly in the CCP BlackBox theater.  Even the costumes take a Filipino turn as the musical unfolds.  I love how Toff and Rep took the reins,  owned this show and called it their own. 

I came into the theater without expectations and left with a joyful heart. Rep is finally back. 

*** #repcarousel2022 runs till Dec 18. I suggest you skip that Christmas party or dinner and go see this show ✨✨✨

Inno, short for Valentinno, came into our lives on Valentine's Day four years ago.  Since then he has filled our home with sooo much love, humor and his own way of being himself. 

When i chose him from a litter of four kittens, I picked him because I saw he had instant rapport with the other babies at home. Inno was playful and got along well with everyone.  Inno was quite naughty, too--he impregnated the whole neighborhood (being true to his name) and I had to spay him because he was contributing to the cat population in the village😂 

Inno was my late night confidante, my unboxing partner,  the judger of the household, our massage therapist, seat warmer, sleeping beauty, Garfield to the neighbors and our baby boy. 

Haven't had the time to mourn his passing but today we laid his ashes in the garden where he loved to be. 

You will be missed, Inno.  Say hello to Juanita and Teacup for us 🤍🤍🤍

#ValentinnoTheCat

New discovery:  A three hour scenic tour of greenery past Dumaguete airport leads you to this hidden gem in Sipalay, Negros Occidental—the newest in the  #signaturecollection of the @discovery_hospitality group. 

You can now add #ManamiResort @manamilife to your list of must go to places in the Philippines for some serious r&r, food and nature tripping.  Manami means beautiful in Ilonggo, it means the same in Japanese. 

With 16 private  villas, 3 dining spaces, a spa plus a cave  right within the property make this an all-in-one luxe hideaway destination.  The service is thoughtful, heartfelt and personal.  Food is fun and yummy, delightful+deliciously Filipino. 

The people behind Manami, Cristina and Andrei Corro, or the Alpha One and Two of the place leave no stone unturned to make your trek and trip an exceptional experience. There is something distinctly Ilonggo in the way they do things, both being from Bacolod.  Anton Corro, Andrei’s brother made us feel right at home with stories of how the place came to be.  A beautifully feathered friend is also a Manami mainstay.

2023 really is a year of new discoveries, and how exciting is it that we get to be tourists in our own country.  Life is Manami, indeed.

Truth be told, been feeling under the weather these past few days.  Getting anxious and pressured about certain things. Needed to get out for a bit and this trip proved to be the perfect escape. 

@manamilife made me breathe some fresh air, re-embrace nature, meet new friends and catch up with a few old ones.  Manami gave me the right reset button and now, I am ready for everything  again. 

Sometimes, a bit of vitamin sea (can’t believe I’m using this in my caption) is all we need. 🌊☀️ 

#manamiresort 
#manamilife 
#signaturecollection

Got emotional as I crossed the finish line raising our flag at today’s @londonmarathon. 

So much sacrifice, blood, sweat and tears led up to this day.  Had second thoughts and wanted to defer to another time—so many things happening at the same time and it was hard to find time to train but glad I pushed through.  Could  have been more prepared but threw all caution to the wind when I thought of the many kids of @smiletrain @smiletrainph that our team could help… and so here we are.  More posts to come! 

#OKtobeUK #londonmarathon #londonmarathon2023

To be perfectly honest, I wasn’t aiming to break any personal records, not gunning for a time goal when I ran this year’s @londonmarathon. 

My intention was to savor every moment, soak in the sights and take my time in running the race. 

My race, my pace. 

The first part was spent with Yaparazzi Smiles teammate @samverzosa and even went with him to Tesco Express to make sure his splinter doesn’t get worse at km15.  Then I followed a Filipino pacer from New York who did a 2km run walk with a whole bunch of others.  But the real beauty of this particular marathon for me is seeing the people run for their advocacies.  Some ran for their loved ones (“running for you, dad!) people with cancer, others for Parkinson’s and saw quite a few running for Alzheimer’s research. 

One ran as a giant telephone and when I read the words on it, it said that she was running for a mental health hotline because her brother committed suicide. 

All 48,000++ runners running with a different story. That’s what makes this marathon extra special. Taught me as I ran along to be kinder, to really take my time getting to know others and myself.  To love this life that God gave us and to nurture and savor every minute that we are alive.

Up where they walk, up where they run, up where they stay all day in the suuuuun. 🎶 

Took an impromptu trip to San Vicente, Palawan via @experiencesunlight and immersed myself in @clubagutaya’s abundant offerings—@piealvarez + @icymarinas’ warm hospitality, @clamoringal’s amazing food (I don’t know where to begin—everything is sooooo good—all farmed here!) and this beautiful stretch of golden beach.  Badly needed this.  Thank you Lord!!! 

#sanvicente #palawan #sunlight #sunlightair #clubagutaya  #sunnysanvic

So this dolphin (false killer whale) swam to the shore in distress—it was disoriented or was injured.  @piealvarez saw it on the shore on our morning walk and @sanvicentegirl @clubagutaya quickly mobilized a team (see IGs) to make sure she is well rested before she could swim out.  We FaceTimed with an NGO that specializes in aquatic creatures and he told us to just make sure it faces the ocean and rests until it can swim back home. 

They stayed with her all day and called the coast guard to monitor as well.  As of last night, she’s still there but not getting better.  Praying for a miracle. 

#sanvicente #palawan #clubagutaya #sunlightair #sunnysanvic #dolphin  #falsekillerwhale

Never thought I could do it, and apparently neither did my companions.  But that weekend, I did my first camping experience in Tanay, Rizal. 

At first I was fazed by the no cellphone signal (until I found where it was) and no air conditioning but the lure of being in the midst of nature and good company far outweighed my perceived need for creature comforts. 

So there we were sharing thoughts, opinions and our diverse life experience under the bright moon, and then some rain and then the stars and then it was time for the next day, our shoot for @terrazas_andes.  Woke up with everyone chirpy and the river right in front of me flowing like the Terrazas wine we had last night and all of today. 

@chefjayps put out one feast after another, from fishball sinigang to sugpo to steak and more, it was a glamping gastronomic feast. @kombibrew kept us up with their yummy coffee, too.  And then @overlandkings surprised us with all the camping gear he brought that took things to another level. 

What I thought was a weekend of work turned out to be an amazing and unforgettable time to bond with newfound friends and chosen family.

BALAY BALETE, constructed using almost two thousand old and discarded water containers, is one of my new works from the ALAMAT exhibition which is currently on display (and free to the public!) at the National Museum of Anthropology. 

‘Balay Balete is an immersive outdoor installation that intricately connects speculative sci-fi, environmental consciousness, and Philippine folkloric beliefs that transcend beyond their precolonial origins. At its heart lies the Balete tree surrounded by mythical creatures that dwell in it - the tik-tik (bird-like human creature), manananggal (vampire-like human creature that feeds on blood and unborn babies), tikbalang (half horse and half man creature), and a white lady (faceless phantom of a woman, usually dressed in white). Together, these supernatural elements and the aswang (shape shifting creature) symbolize the reclamation of our ancient, but still existing beliefs distorted by colonialism.' 
*See last photo for full exhibition notes 

It takes a village to bring projects like these to life. I’d like to thank my team of artists, sculptors, builders, and project managers who helped create the work. 

Produced in collaboration with @officialtimyap as part of @shakerattleandball. #shakerattleandball

NO EXCUSES! 

I stand in solidarity with women all over the world against any form of gender based violence.

Did you know that 1 in 3 women will experience some form for violence in their lifetime? Violence takes many forms - sexual, emotional, psychological and mental. These are forms of violence.

I have witnessed a few women in my life who have encountered this kind of abuse and we must put a stop to it.  I remember standing up to a man and telling him to stop.  It’s not easy but we need to do it. 

“It was an accident” 
“It won’t happen again” 
“I was tired from work” 
“You made me do it”

All these excuses end now. There is #NOExcuse for violence.

I encourage all of us to help each other, stand together. Let us UNITE and have each other’s backs.

. . . 

I encourage you to post your own solidarity message and tag @unwomenasia @unwomen 

#16Days
#WalangPalusot
#BabaeMayLabanKa
#UNWomenPH

If you need help, 911 is now equipped to assist in gender based violence emergencies.

For more information:

16 Days — https://www.unwomen.org/en/what-we-do/ending-violence-against-women 

Philippine Anti VAWC law — https://lawphil.net/statutes/repacts/ra2004/ra_9262_2004.html

2023 went by real fast.  Looked through my phone memory to remember all the moments that went by, events that I hosted, campaigns that we produced and happenings we all attended non stop.  It was a whirlwind of break ups and breakthroughs, one coming right after another. 

It was a sprint and a marathon at the same time.  A roller coaster ride disguised as a spa session, an extended cold plunge right after the extreme heat of the steam room. 

Through it all, what I’ve learned is that it’s not about the speed of how you do things but how you enjoy and savor each moment given.  Even the difficult times, through disappointment over friends, things not going your way and some other unexpected curve balls, I have grown to savor each one and ask myself what every  situation is teaching me. 

Another thing I’ve realized is that life is really not perfect (even if in social media it seems like it—far from it!) and that nothing is paved for you. So you gotta focus, work harder, be solutions-oriented and think differently to achieve your desired results. 

Above all, know when to rest, don’t take sides and always be grateful.  Thank you 2023! 

#thankyou2023
